  "prompt": "Where online can I use my Maestro card?",
  "response": "Maestro cards, which are a type of debit card issued by Mastercard, are widely accepted at various online merchants and platforms globally. However, acceptance can vary depending on the merchant's policies and the region. Here are some common places where you can typically use your Maestro card online:\n\n1. **E-commerce Websites**:\n   - Amazon\n   - eBay\n   - Walmart\n   - ASOS\n   - Zalando\n\n2. **Travel and Accommodation**:\n   - Booking.com\n   - Expedia\n   - Airbnb\n   - Skyscanner\n\n3. **Grocery and Food Delivery**:\n   - Instacart\n   - Deliveroo\n   - Uber Eats\n   - HelloFresh\n\n4. **Subscription Services**:\n   - Netflix\n   - Spotify\n   - Adobe Creative Cloud\n   - Microsoft 365\n\n5. **Utility Bills and Services**:\n   - PayPal (you can link your Maestro card)\n   - Google Pay\n   - Apple Pay (in some regions)\n\n6. **Retail Stores**:\n   - H&M\n   - Zara\n   - Best Buy\n   - IKEA\n\n7. **Charity Donations**:\n   - UNICEF\n   - Red Cross\n   - WWF\n\n8. **Gaming Platforms**:\n   - Steam\n   - PlayStation Store\n   - Xbox Live\n\n9. **Miscellaneous**:\n   - Online ticketing for events (e.g., Eventbrite)\n   - Educational platforms (e.g., Coursera, Udemy)\n\nPlease note that while Maestro cards are widely accepted, some online merchants might only accept credit cards or other forms of payment. It's always a good idea to check the payment options on the merchant's website before attempting to make a purchase.\n\nAdditionally, as of recent updates, Mastercard has been phasing out the Maestro brand in favor of the more modern Debit Mastercard. Therefore, if you encounter issues, you might want to consider getting a Debit Mastercard for broader acceptance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
